WEBVTT

00:00.130 --> 00:03.294
not be scattered over the face of the whole earth.

00:04.556 --> 00:09.343
But the Lord came down to see the city and the tower that the men were building.

00:09.884 --> 00:21.360
The Lord said, if as one people speaking the same language, they have begun to do this, then nothing they plan to do will be impossible for them.

00:22.381 --> 00:28.530
Come, let us go down and confuse our language so that they will not understand each other.

00:29.282 --> 00:35.309
So the Lord scattered them from there over all the earth, and they stopped building the city.

00:36.069 --> 00:44.018
That is why it was called Babel, because there the Lord confused the language of the whole world.

00:44.418 --> 00:51.866
From there the Lord scattered them over the face of the whole earth.

00:53.008 --> 00:53.568
Thank you, Stan.

00:54.169 --> 00:58.834
Before I look into today's message, I'd like to introduce that new family I mentioned earlier.

00:58.946 --> 01:04.133
This is Danny and his wife, Kathy, right over there.

01:04.353 --> 01:06.216
And they're four children.

01:06.256 --> 01:08.239
The youngest one just went to Children's Church.

01:08.819 --> 01:10.281
So good to have you all with us.

01:11.183 --> 01:12.625
And let's give them a hand.

01:16.710 --> 01:20.635
We give all first time guests, one of our Canvas bag, and it has some treats in it.

01:20.695 --> 01:22.278
But it has a registration card.

01:22.298 --> 01:23.680
We fill that out and drop in the offering later.

01:23.700 --> 01:24.320
We'd appreciate it.

01:25.202 --> 01:25.402
OK?

01:26.223 --> 01:28.466
If you have your sermon outlines, go ahead and take that out.

01:28.674 --> 01:35.624
And again, if you've been here the last couple of Sundays, you know, I kept postponing this message, which was supposed to be given two weeks ago.

01:36.345 --> 01:38.548
Two weeks ago, I was really sick, so I had a guest speaker.

01:39.330 --> 01:46.180
Last Sunday, my brain was really fried from dealing with some things that were happening, some urgent needs I had to take care of.

01:47.221 --> 01:51.848
So anyway, I promise I'd do it today and hopefully we'll make it through today.

01:52.689 --> 01:55.954
Maybe a shorter sermon because of the communion.

01:56.290 --> 02:00.756
But again, if you have your swimmer outline, something to write with to fill in the blanks, as we go along, that'd be great.

02:02.940 --> 02:09.730
Usually when we think of the whole concept of unity among people, we think of it as in positive terms.

02:09.810 --> 02:12.253
It's a good thing when people get together and are united.

02:12.754 --> 02:18.322
However, this is an example in the Old Testament where the people who were alive at the time

02:18.402 --> 02:23.447
All got together, but unfortunately, this was a negative example of unity.

02:23.827 --> 02:29.052
And the reason why it was negative was because of the purpose and the reason they were gathering together.

02:29.573 --> 02:33.016
It was basically an opposition of God and God's word.

02:33.396 --> 02:40.283
And whenever that happens, unfortunately, it still happens today in smaller ways, even among so-called Christians.

02:40.903 --> 02:47.890
And when that happens, we need to have the discernment in the God's wisdom and understanding that that is not a good thing.

02:47.970 --> 02:51.035
and basically don't be involved in it.

02:51.096 --> 02:53.179
But we're going to look at this this morning.

02:53.460 --> 03:00.332
Many of us have heard the story before, Tower of Babel, and how God confused their language up to this time.

03:00.372 --> 03:02.937
They all had the same language.

03:02.957 --> 03:07.906
Remember, Noah and the Flood, God judged the entire world because of all the sin and wickedness.

03:08.346 --> 03:12.594
Just Noah and his wife, three sons, their wives survived in the ark.

03:12.834 --> 03:20.005
and they were repopulating the earth and God told them, commanded them to spread through and populate the whole world.

03:20.326 --> 03:28.518
But they, for whatever reason, after a number of generations, the people totally ignored what God was saying and had their own plans.

03:28.979 --> 03:31.944
And this is what we see here in Genesis chapter 11.

03:33.326 --> 03:38.674
The first blank to fill in is what I just mentioned, the God's command to populate the earth.

03:38.978 --> 03:50.893
God had actually given that command to Adam and Eve back in the Garden of Eden in Genesis chapter 1, verse 28, and then again to know in his family after the flood in Genesis chapter 9.

03:51.694 --> 04:01.947
But it's unfortunate that again after a number of generations, these people again had straight away from following God and were in total opposition to God and His Word.

04:02.528 --> 04:07.314
So number two in your outline, people they choose to make their own plan

04:07.714 --> 04:10.677
and a name for themselves.

04:11.078 --> 04:12.960
That's the blank to fill in, for themselves.

04:14.161 --> 04:19.768
Instead of living for the name of God and to honor Him, they were determined to basically do their own thing.

04:20.909 --> 04:23.813
They understood God told them to spread out, populate the earth.

04:23.833 --> 04:25.094
They said, now we're not going to do that.

04:25.354 --> 04:35.346
We're going to gather together in this area that God called Babel, but actually many scholars believe that really this area is ancient Babylon.

04:35.682 --> 04:45.894
The many of you have heard of that term Babylon, and as a matter of fact, in the Bible, it became almost a synonym, sort of a catchphrase for a place of evil.

04:46.694 --> 04:53.442
And it's kind of like, you know, many of you have heard, if you've been around for years, you know, that my wife and I, many times we go on vacation to Las Vegas.

04:54.003 --> 05:04.114
And I also feel like I have to give an explanation to people, as a minister, when I say, you know, we're going on vacation to Vegas for a week or two, whatever, and people, it's kind of like a razor eyebrows, I'll be like,

05:04.290 --> 05:06.593
Okay, the minister is going to Vegas.

05:06.694 --> 05:08.516
He likes to go to Vegas a lot.

05:09.117 --> 05:09.318
Why?

05:09.358 --> 05:11.040
Because Vegas is known as what?

05:11.060 --> 05:12.282
What's the nickname for Las Vegas?

05:12.542 --> 05:14.425
The Sin City, all right?

05:14.445 --> 05:15.207
The Sin City.

05:15.727 --> 05:17.129
Yeah, the good choice, Pachalois.

05:17.650 --> 05:22.377
Anyway, the reason why we go there is because there's very cheap housing, always available year round.

05:22.758 --> 05:27.926
There's millions of time shares in the hotel rooms, wherever you can find great deals just about anytime.

05:28.306 --> 05:30.770
But there are also some beautiful, natural

05:30.882 --> 05:32.424
parks nearby.

05:32.625 --> 05:42.439
Some of you have been to Red Rock, which is only a 20-minute drive west of Vegas, as well as Valley of Fire, which is a state park about an hour drive northeast of Vegas.

05:43.100 --> 05:50.471
And we like to hike, and we do go to the casinos once in a while, have a buffet, whatever, but Las Vegas is known as the Sin City.

05:50.952 --> 06:00.626
Well, if they're known as the Sin City, because in Nevada, I think everybody's aware, it's not only legal for gambling, but prostitution is legal in Nevada.

06:00.898 --> 06:03.141
And you know, it's kind of weird.

06:03.161 --> 06:07.006
You think you're 50 states one state actually has legal prostitution.

06:07.046 --> 06:08.108
That's Nevada.

06:08.609 --> 06:10.812
So Vegas is known as the Sin City.

06:10.832 --> 06:16.940
Well, believe me, Las Vegas is nothing compared to what ancient Babylon became.

06:17.421 --> 06:24.410
Ancient Babylon became known as, as I said, the Bible used it as a reference to a place of evil.

06:24.470 --> 06:26.473
That's how bad it really became.

06:27.435 --> 06:29.938
The word Babylon actually

06:30.498 --> 06:37.385
It literally was meant to convey the gateway to God.

06:38.306 --> 06:43.130
And this kind of conveys the mentality of these people that wanted to build a tower into the heavens.

06:43.571 --> 06:45.933
They wanted to make a name for themselves.

06:46.394 --> 06:53.340
They basically said, not only do we not need God, not only do we not want to obey God, we're going to be like God ourselves.

06:54.101 --> 06:59.026
And so that's why Babylon, the very name of the ancient city of Babylon,

06:59.202 --> 07:01.426
literally met the gateway to heaven.

07:01.826 --> 07:04.470
They're going to build this tower right into heaven.

07:06.454 --> 07:16.670
So as I said before, unity among people is generally a good thing but really depends and what we have to discern is what is the nature and what is the purpose of that unity.

07:17.531 --> 07:26.706
And we're going to see in just a moment the God is the one who brings about real genuine unity that lasts forever.

07:26.882 --> 07:30.547
And that is through a personal relationship with Jesus Christ.

07:30.967 --> 07:33.530
This is what God has established in the church.

07:33.570 --> 07:38.076
The universal church ever since Jesus came was crucified, was raised from the dead.

07:38.557 --> 07:42.541
He establishes the spiritual entity called the church.

07:43.062 --> 07:55.858
Every single man, woman and child for the last 2000 years that has come to faith in Jesus Christ is automatically spiritually joined to this entity called the church, capital C.

07:56.354 --> 08:03.083
Now some people get confused in the New Testament when it refers to the church, capital C, that's the universal church.

08:03.103 --> 08:09.272
Every believer in the entire world ever since Jesus was resurrected to the time he comes back.

08:09.793 --> 08:16.883
That's the church, universal church, capital C. Church small literacy, lowercase C, is a local church.

08:17.343 --> 08:22.130
Kind of like Chinese community churches, one of thousands of local churches.

08:22.274 --> 08:30.886
where real believers assemble, but we don't know if everybody that comes to Chinese Community Church or any local church is really a believer.

08:31.387 --> 08:32.609
That's between them and God.

08:33.210 --> 08:35.613
Some people come to church for all kinds of other reasons.

08:36.394 --> 08:47.250
And there are many so called Christian churches because the things that they maybe believe and the things they teach and the things they propagate are totally contrary to the Bible.

08:47.714 --> 08:52.339
There are so-called Christian churches that do not even believe the Bible is the Word of God.

08:52.780 --> 08:55.603
They don't even believe God is the only God of the universe.

08:55.984 --> 08:58.847
They don't believe that Jesus is the only way for salvation.

08:59.388 --> 09:04.113
And these are the core beliefs of what we call evangelical Christians.

09:04.614 --> 09:11.241
Evangelical Christians have a certain core of beliefs about God, about the Bible, and about the Christian faith.

09:12.282 --> 09:15.346
Those are the kinds of Christians that we want to have

09:15.426 --> 09:18.249
unity with because that's the unity that God has created.

09:20.051 --> 09:31.302
It's tempting, you know, even among Christians, even among those of us who are ministers, to want to make a name for ourselves sometimes more than living and serving the name of Jesus Christ.

09:31.763 --> 09:34.646
That is human nature, and we all have to struggle with it.

09:35.467 --> 09:42.514
I was involved in some of you may remember I mentioned this before, I had the opportunity of being involved in gathering

09:42.658 --> 09:50.667
Asian-American leaders from all over the country for a very special conference back in 2004 and in 2008, down in Southern California.

09:51.108 --> 10:05.484
Over 400 Asian-American leaders came from all over the country, even a few from Hawaii, you know, together, because it had never happened before to have Asian-American pastors and church leaders and Christian leaders from all over the country gather for a three-day conference.

10:05.504 --> 10:10.290
And I have the privilege of being sort of the one who helped facilitate all of that.

10:10.722 --> 10:12.305
And it was such a blessing.

10:12.365 --> 10:17.594
And during the conference, the three-day conference, I was kind of more low-key in serving the background most of the time.

10:17.654 --> 10:19.016
And that was fine with me.

10:19.777 --> 10:24.445
But years later, I was at another church meeting with some Asian-American leaders.

10:24.726 --> 10:27.270
And I was in an elevator going up in this hotel.

10:27.330 --> 10:29.935
And I heard two pastors who didn't really know me.

10:29.955 --> 10:36.466
And I heard them discussing this wonderful conference they had attended in Los Angeles back in 2004.

10:37.026 --> 10:44.657
And I was behind him, and they didn't know me, and I was really tempted to sort of just tap them on the show and say, oh yeah, that was a really good conference, wasn't it?

10:44.737 --> 10:46.840
I'm the one who kind of put it all together.

10:48.623 --> 10:51.046
Just by the way, I mean, just to see you know.

10:52.248 --> 10:53.189
That was really tempting.

10:53.910 --> 10:54.591
I got a myth.

10:54.711 --> 11:00.940
In the flesh, you know, it's like, yeah, you know, God used me for this, but hey, you know, they should know.

11:01.180 --> 11:04.245
They should know that they're standing in the elevator, the person who killed them.

11:04.265 --> 11:05.106
For what reason?

11:05.378 --> 11:11.646
For what possible purpose would that serve for the glory of God and for the purposes of God?

11:11.806 --> 11:14.489
How would that be important that they know that I had something to do with it?

11:14.970 --> 11:15.771
Absolutely nothing.

11:16.432 --> 11:17.533
Really, nothing.

11:18.314 --> 11:18.935
It was tempting.

11:19.555 --> 11:25.623
And thank God, He gave me enough self-control and insight to realize, don't say anything, Lewis.

11:26.164 --> 11:28.306
You don't have to say anything to these people.

11:28.867 --> 11:34.674
Just be blessed that they had a great time, that it was encouraging to them, and thank God for it.

11:35.170 --> 11:37.252
because that's really important.

11:37.272 --> 11:40.736
And by the way, some of you know, I've been here at the church for over nine years.

11:41.277 --> 11:50.187
You may also know that we're putting together a search committee because I'm 64 this summer and it's time for the church to go through the transition of finding a new pastor.

11:50.367 --> 11:58.456
Well, I'll tell you, it was kind of funny because a couple of years ago somebody showed me a list of all the past ministers of this church, just church is what, over 95 years old.

11:59.057 --> 12:03.442
And it was a complete list of all the previous ministers and how many years they had served.

12:03.778 --> 12:05.220
Okay, here's another temptation.

12:05.240 --> 12:19.274
I'm looking at the list, and I'm trying to count out how many years each person had served, and I'm looking at thinking, you know, if I can last maybe another year or two, I'll have the longest term of service here at Chinese communities.

12:19.735 --> 12:21.877
And then I thought, stupid!

12:22.658 --> 12:23.339
Who cares?

12:23.579 --> 12:24.960
Who cares how long you've been here?

12:25.140 --> 12:25.581
Who cares?

12:25.601 --> 12:26.782
Are you even a pastor here?

12:27.083 --> 12:30.386
You see, ultimately, and I know we're humanly speaking,

12:30.466 --> 12:33.610
It always feels good to be remembered and to be appreciated.

12:33.690 --> 12:39.617
And I certainly appreciate all of the appreciation that you have shown as a church family over the years.

12:39.878 --> 12:40.158
Really.

12:40.459 --> 12:48.969
I mean, this church family is just off the charts in terms of a church that is really grateful and shows their appreciation in so many tangible ways.

12:49.069 --> 12:50.111
I am so blessed by that.

12:50.531 --> 12:56.018
But you know, quite frankly, if I'm really focused on what God has for me as a minister,

12:56.226 --> 13:03.416
And this is something that all of us need to have a focus as a child of God, someone who has a personal relationship with God through faith in Jesus Christ.

13:03.436 --> 13:04.517
You know the only thing that really matters?

13:04.778 --> 13:09.544
It doesn't matter if anybody knows us or our name or even our church name.

13:10.406 --> 13:17.916
All that matters is that people would somehow be joined close and just drawn closer to who Jesus Christ is.

13:18.717 --> 13:22.322
And that they would exalt him in every aspect of their being.

13:22.658 --> 13:27.745
If they forget our names or the name of our church or the name of our denominator, those things don't even matter.

13:28.225 --> 13:28.866
They really don't.

13:29.547 --> 13:33.292
All that matters is that we live for the name of Jesus Christ.

13:33.773 --> 13:35.735
He is the king of kings, the Lord of lords.

13:36.036 --> 13:38.539
He's the almighty creator of the universe.

13:38.559 --> 13:40.742
And he's the one that gets all the glory in the eye.

13:40.762 --> 13:50.194
Remember, in the New Testament, God tells us that someday, someday in the future, every knee shall bow and every tongue confess.

13:50.882 --> 14:01.734
Doesn't matter if you're an atheist or whatever, God says someday every knee is going to bow, every tongue confess that Jesus Christ is Lord.

14:02.755 --> 14:05.298
We have the privilege of doing that now.

14:05.858 --> 14:08.902
We don't have to wait until we're forced to do it by God someday in judgment.

14:09.262 --> 14:10.644
Now we can do it willfully now.

14:10.704 --> 14:16.530
We can choose to acknowledge and to worship and to serve and to live for the Almighty God of the universe.

14:17.538 --> 14:20.783
We have that opportunity and that privilege, as I explained last week.

14:22.926 --> 14:24.969
God has this great news for us.

14:25.109 --> 14:32.199
In a moment, we'll celebrate what Jesus did for us through the memorial that's called Communion, the Lord's Table.

14:33.301 --> 14:35.424
It reminds us of what Jesus did for us.

14:36.024 --> 14:38.889
The Son of God died for our sin.

14:38.909 --> 14:40.831
He rose from the dead.

14:40.851 --> 14:42.674
He's alive today.

14:43.106 --> 14:49.893
And all we need to do to become a believer, to become a child of God, is to put our faith and trust in Jesus Christ.

14:50.414 --> 14:54.899
To trust that He is God's Son, He died for my sin, He rose from the dead.

14:55.900 --> 14:59.424
That's all is required to become a Christian and to have eternal life.

14:59.764 --> 15:01.126
God makes it so easy.

15:01.666 --> 15:03.048
And I don't know, it's unfortunate.

15:03.108 --> 15:08.253
So many people have made it so much more complicated and added all kinds of things.

15:08.273 --> 15:12.498
You know, yeah, you got to believe in Jesus, but you also have to do this, this, this, no!

15:12.962 --> 15:15.526
God says it's simple faith and trust.

15:16.467 --> 15:19.812
Ephesians chapter 2, for by grace are you saved through faith.

15:20.533 --> 15:26.781
None of yourselves, it is a gift of God, not of works, lest any man boast.

15:27.422 --> 15:34.632
If we had to do anything to add to our salvation, be a good person, come to church, read your Bible, you know, do all this.

15:34.652 --> 15:35.794
If you had to do anything,

15:36.322 --> 15:43.255
Then if you did it and then you went to heaven, you could sort a brag about it and say, well, I'm going to heaven and then this person is not because I was a good person.

15:43.275 --> 15:44.777
I had nothing to do with it.

15:46.100 --> 15:48.264
And I realized some Christians are very confused by this.

15:48.284 --> 15:50.347
They say, well, it doesn't matter if you're a good person or not.

15:50.728 --> 15:53.653
Of course, it's better to be a good person even if you're not a believer.

15:54.315 --> 15:56.238
But that's not going to get you to heaven.

15:56.258 --> 16:00.626
The only way we get to heaven is, number one, if you're absolutely perfect.

16:01.026 --> 16:08.016
If you were exactly like Jesus Christ every moment of every day for your entire life, you get to heaven because you have never sinned.

16:08.817 --> 16:10.620
But that would be contrary to what the Bible says.

16:10.660 --> 16:12.142
The Bible says all have sinned.

16:12.543 --> 16:14.385
We all fall short of the glory of God.

16:14.926 --> 16:16.168
The wages of sin is death.

16:16.809 --> 16:21.095
But the free gift of God is eternal life through Jesus Christ our Lord.

16:21.596 --> 16:23.378
Simple faith and trust in Him.

16:23.398 --> 16:25.842
And so when we take communion,

16:25.954 --> 16:34.745
Usually every month when we take communion, I always try to just prepare everybody by reminding everyone, first of all, what the elements represent, the bread and the juice.

16:34.765 --> 16:37.349
They represent the body and the blood of Jesus Christ.

16:38.010 --> 16:39.652
And why do we partake of these things?

16:39.772 --> 16:43.337
Because Jesus, he's the one who set up this whole memorial.

16:43.797 --> 16:53.650
He wanted his followers to remember in a very tangible way the spiritual realities that he died for our sin.

16:54.114 --> 16:56.397
He made this incredible sacrifice.

16:56.417 --> 16:59.720
God sent His only Son to become the Lamb of God.

17:00.641 --> 17:06.327
All the thousands and hundreds of thousands of animals that were slaughtered in the Old Testament by the Jewish people.

17:06.828 --> 17:13.656
Those were all symbols looking forward to the cross when Jesus Christ would be the Lamb of God.

17:14.076 --> 17:21.164
Now believers, the last 2000 years, when we take communion in the Lord's table, we look back to the cross.

17:22.065 --> 17:23.186
All of human history.

17:23.330 --> 17:25.933
revolves around the cross of Jesus Christ.

17:27.154 --> 17:28.596
Look forward to the Old Testament.

17:28.936 --> 17:32.300
New Testament looks back to the cross of Jesus Christ.

17:33.461 --> 17:36.725
So the Tower of Babel, these people decided they were going to make a name for themselves.

17:36.865 --> 17:38.427
They're going to ignore God as word.

17:39.308 --> 17:42.992
And as I said earlier, God's the one who establishes real unity.

17:43.012 --> 17:50.460
And by the way, when God judges the people, when he confused their languages, so they dispersed, and now they started to populate the earth.

17:50.581 --> 17:51.922
Now they're going to fulfill.

17:52.002 --> 17:54.145
what God intended them to do in the first place.

17:54.746 --> 17:56.949
That's just a reminder that God is sovereign.

17:57.610 --> 18:03.798
Meaning even if people want to disobey God, He is going to accomplish His purposes one way or the other.

18:04.759 --> 18:15.294
Either we can cooperate and we can obey by faith and we can accomplish God's purposes, or God is going to bring judgment and discipline and He will accomplish His purposes.

18:15.514 --> 18:18.578
He wanted the earth populated, it gets populated.

18:19.219 --> 18:21.522
Not because people obeyed Him,

18:21.794 --> 18:26.440
Listen to him, but through God's judgment, he brings confusion into their languages.

18:27.081 --> 18:30.426
Some of you are familiar with a Christian ministry called Wycliffe Bible Translators.

18:30.486 --> 18:31.607
They've been around quite a while.

18:32.088 --> 18:39.718
Their whole goal and mission is to bring the Word of God into every known human language around the world.

18:40.559 --> 18:46.267
And my wife and I have had the privilege of supporting some missionary friends with Wycliffe for over 40 years.

18:47.168 --> 18:51.634
We met them when we were in Bible College in seminary in Dallas, Texas, and we've been supporting them ever since.

18:52.034 --> 19:01.304
You know how many, I just saw the newsletter recently, and they're trying to log and just count how many known human languages are out there in the world today.

19:01.664 --> 19:13.036
You know, everybody want to guess, you know, there's over 7,000 human languages now is how many of them have even a portion of the word of God, say the gospel of John even, not even half.

19:13.096 --> 19:18.962
So, I mean, there's so much work to be done because, you know, obviously we believe the word of God, the Bible,

19:19.106 --> 19:25.155
is so essential to people to come to know God and to grow in their personal faith with Jesus Christ.

19:25.956 --> 19:27.939
So God brought the judgment of the Tower of Babel.

19:27.959 --> 19:28.780
It disperses them.

19:29.080 --> 19:34.648
They start populating the earth because that was God's sovereign purpose in the first place.

19:35.549 --> 19:47.186
The last point of your outline, God's judgment and eventual plan for unity among people, Genesis chapter 11, again, as I said, he disperses them.

19:47.330 --> 19:51.234
But in Galatians chapter three, if we could bring that up real quick, please.

19:52.055 --> 19:54.637
Galatians chapter three, verses 26 to 28.

19:54.777 --> 20:11.474
Here's what it talks about, the unity, and by the way, if you've been around here a while, you know that many times I've mentioned, one of many blessings that I've experienced here at the church is the unity that we have, especially among the church leadership.

20:12.194 --> 20:16.018
If you haven't been to a lot of other churches, you perhaps are unaware

20:16.098 --> 20:20.926
that that is one of the number one problems that churches in America experience.

20:20.946 --> 20:35.891
A lack of unity among leadership, whether it's the pastors or the lay leaders or all of them together when they have a church board, among ministers, when they talk about their board meetings, it's usually like a nightmare.

20:36.372 --> 20:42.642
They're usually talking about horrible, horrible conflicts that they experience in their board meetings.

20:42.818 --> 20:58.903
And I'm sitting there for the last nine years, every time I'm with these fellowship meetings, and I've learned to sort of tone down my enthusiasm and my bubbly expression, because it sort of discourages some of my Christian ministry friends.

20:59.284 --> 21:08.578
Because I tell them, man, you're not gonna believe that the last years I've been here at Christ's University, we have these lay leaders and we work together, we actually enjoy our board meetings.

21:10.261 --> 21:11.122
Look at me like,

21:12.162 --> 21:13.303
You enjoy them?

21:13.443 --> 21:18.728
I mean, you know, to endure them would, for many of them, that would be a blessing, just to be able to endure it.

21:18.989 --> 21:20.790
I said, no, no, we laugh, we have a great time.

21:21.471 --> 21:24.754
We just have this amazing spirit of unity and harmony.

21:25.655 --> 21:28.798
And it's like, wow, you know, it is such a blessing.

21:29.479 --> 21:36.506
God has blessed this church with an amazing group of lay leaders and how we can serve together.

21:36.826 --> 21:41.170
And then the congregation as a whole, how we serve together like a family.

21:41.666 --> 21:44.709
And we know that families have their struggles sometimes.

21:45.009 --> 21:57.902
But the last nine plus years I've been here, this church family in terms of the spirit of unity as we live and serve and try to honor our God has just been amazing and such a blessing.

21:58.542 --> 22:01.585
But Galatians chapter three, thanks for bringing up Josh.

22:02.066 --> 22:07.631
Verse 26, you are all sons of God, how through faith in Christ Jesus.

22:07.892 --> 22:10.354
Verse 27, for all of you,

22:10.658 --> 22:12.300
who were baptized in the Christ.

22:12.341 --> 22:14.584
That's what happens when you put your faith and trust in Christ.

22:14.964 --> 22:19.151
The Holy Spirit baptized us into the body of Christ, even though we may not be aware of it.

22:19.351 --> 22:20.112
We learn it by later.

22:20.853 --> 22:23.798
We're baptized in the Christ of clothe yourselves with Christ.

22:23.958 --> 22:26.582
Again, it's all about our relationship to Jesus Christ.

22:26.982 --> 22:36.336
Verse 28, there is neither Jude or Greek, slave nor free, male nor female, for you are all one in Christ Jesus.

22:36.977 --> 22:37.939
That almost understands.

22:37.959 --> 22:40.082
Some people have looked at that verse and they said, see?

22:40.578 --> 22:48.386
We shouldn't even talk about the fact that we have different races, or different ethnic groups, or different cultures, or that we have male and female.

22:48.946 --> 22:50.048
Because look at that verse.

22:50.128 --> 22:52.610
It says, no, it doesn't mean it's done away with.

22:53.531 --> 23:04.862
It means that with all these human distinctions, there is this new sense of unity and harmony in the body of Christ when we are joined together because of our faith in Jesus Christ.

23:05.543 --> 23:08.466
And that is one of the most amazing testimonies

23:08.546 --> 23:13.031
about the reality of who God is and what Jesus Christ can do among people.

23:13.571 --> 23:19.778
It is when there is unity and harmony among a lot of different people who are from many different backgrounds.

23:20.459 --> 23:31.871
And, you know, our Tuesday night men's lives tonight, I mentioned that before, God has brought different brothers in Christ from other churches that don't have a men's group, and our Tuesday night men's group is very diverse racially.

23:32.552 --> 23:38.098
Even though it's a relatively small group, anywhere from six to eight to 12, whatever, almost every week,

23:38.370 --> 23:42.955
We have three or four of all the major racial groups in our nation represented.

23:43.395 --> 23:51.444
We have Asians, we have Caucasians, we have African-American, we have Hispanic, and it's just an amazing diversity that we experience as men.

23:52.265 --> 23:58.272
If you're one of the men here and you've never come to one of our Tuesday night men's vibes, I encourage you to check it out.

23:58.672 --> 24:01.976
Everybody's welcome seven o'clock to eight thirty.

24:03.217 --> 24:04.178
Great type of fellowship.

24:05.122 --> 24:07.325
But this is the kind of unity that God has created.

24:07.365 --> 24:08.526
God's the one who creates it.

24:08.867 --> 24:10.169
We don't create the unity.

24:10.589 --> 24:12.892
We only preserve it and maintain it.

24:13.573 --> 24:16.076
It's our job to preserve the unity that God has created.

24:16.937 --> 24:30.695
But we of all the distinctions, and again, our church board, brothers and sisters serving together, again, having that kind of unity that God has created that honors him, that is a testimony to the world around us.

24:32.878 --> 24:32.978
Okay?

24:33.474 --> 24:39.601
So the blanks again, number one, God's command to populate the earth who was ignored, disobeyed by these people.

24:39.941 --> 24:42.384
They wanted to build a tower, make a name for themselves.

24:43.045 --> 24:50.032
God brings judgment, confuses their language, disperses them all over the earth as he had wanted them to do in the first place.

24:52.295 --> 24:56.059
So God's judgment and eventual plan for unity among people is accomplished.

24:56.960 --> 24:57.220
All right?

24:57.781 --> 25:02.226
We're going to transition into preparing for communion in just a moment.

25:02.402 --> 25:08.047
You generally read a couple of verses from 1 Corinthians chapter 11.

25:08.087 --> 25:13.372
And just a reminder again, as I mentioned earlier, what is communion?

25:14.453 --> 25:22.061
It is a practice that Jesus established to his disciples to remember.

25:22.141 --> 25:25.924
The whole focus of communion is to remember, to remember, to remember what?

25:26.265 --> 25:28.747
To remember Jesus Christ is God's Son.

25:29.227 --> 25:30.348
He died for our sin.

25:30.388 --> 25:32.050
He rose from the dead.

25:32.706 --> 25:35.790
And so we practice a Chinese community church here at our church.

25:35.810 --> 25:40.397
We practice what's called open communion, which means you don't have to be a member of this church.

25:40.417 --> 25:42.080
You don't even have to be a regular tender of this church.

25:42.520 --> 25:48.208
If you know Jesus Christ as your personal Lord and savior, we invite you to partake of the elements with us.

25:49.891 --> 26:00.466
If you're sitting here today and you're not sure if you have a personal relationship with Christ, then when we need to have a moment of prayer in just a moment, you can actually become a Christian

26:01.474 --> 26:02.716
even during that little prayer time.

26:03.137 --> 26:06.041
All you gotta do is say, God, I wanna know you.

26:06.402 --> 26:07.924
I wanna have a personal relationship with you.

26:08.004 --> 26:10.448
I wanna trust in your son, Jesus Christ.

26:11.350 --> 26:15.156
And I believe that Jesus died from my sin and that he rose from the dead.

26:15.837 --> 26:19.282
And when you pray that little prayer to God, that's what it means to become a Christian.

26:19.663 --> 26:21.446
That's all that you need to do.

26:22.107 --> 26:29.138
And then when you partake of the elements, you'll be remembering, perhaps for the very first time, all that Jesus has done for us.

26:29.538 --> 26:31.400
If you're not ready yet to become a Christian, that's okay.

26:31.821 --> 26:32.562
Just stay seated.

26:33.443 --> 26:34.624
Nobody's looking around, whatever.

26:34.644 --> 26:40.752
This is just for those who have a personal relationship with Jesus Christ and are walking in fellowship with Him today.

26:41.673 --> 26:43.976
Okay, let me read a couple of these verses and then we'll pray.

26:44.937 --> 26:52.826
And then when the music starts, what we ask people to do is come out of their pews and form two lines here in the center aisle.

26:53.387 --> 26:55.730
Each line leads to one of these two tables.

26:55.842 --> 27:07.133
And when you come to the table, just pause either as individuals or as a little family, whatever you'd like to do, take a piece of the bread, dip it carefully into the juice, and just partake right up here at the table.

27:07.634 --> 27:10.677
And then when you're done, return to your seats using the outer aisles.

27:12.098 --> 27:18.104
Let me just read 1 Corinthians 11 for all of us in verse 23.

27:18.284 --> 27:24.050
The Apostle Paul says, for I received from the Lord

27:24.194 --> 27:25.755
what I also passed on to you.

27:25.775 --> 27:35.284
The Lord Jesus on the night he was betrayed, took bread, and when he had given thanks, he broke it and said, this is my body, which is for you.

27:35.344 --> 27:37.947
Do this in remembrance of me.

27:37.967 --> 27:44.833
In the same way after supper, he took the cup saying, this cup is the new covenant in my blood.

27:45.454 --> 27:48.056
Do this whenever you drink it in remembrance of me.

27:48.076 --> 27:54.002
For whenever you eat this bread and drink this cup, you proclaim the Lord's death.

27:54.210 --> 27:54.971
until he comes.

27:55.632 --> 28:00.357
So again, just take a little piece of the bread, dip it into the juice, and partake of it right up here at the table.

28:00.997 --> 28:01.678
Take your time.

28:01.778 --> 28:02.539
We got plenty of time.

28:02.579 --> 28:03.200
No big rush.

28:04.121 --> 28:05.682
But let's go ahead and have a word of prayer.

28:05.742 --> 28:14.192
And as I said, if you're here today and you're not sure if you have a personal relationship with Christ, you can pray to receive Jesus Christ right now during my prayer.

28:15.113 --> 28:15.993
No fancy words.

28:16.514 --> 28:17.415
God knows our hearts.

28:17.996 --> 28:23.922
Just tell God you trust in his son, Jesus, as my personal Lord and Savior.

28:24.162 --> 28:27.845
You believe that he died for your sin, and he rose from the dead.

28:28.366 --> 28:31.509
That's all that you need to do to become a Christian.

28:31.529 --> 28:32.470
Okay, so let's pray together.

28:32.550 --> 28:33.811
All heads bowed, eyes closed.

28:34.472 --> 28:35.313
Okay, let's pray together.

28:35.353 --> 28:38.415
Our Father God, thanks so much for who you are.

28:38.456 --> 28:44.161
You are the great God of the universe who created everything that exists, including every one of us here today.

28:45.002 --> 28:49.526
Father, you love us so much that you sent your only son, Jesus, to die for us.

28:50.207 --> 28:53.810
He died for all of our sin, and then he rose from the dead.

28:54.146 --> 29:07.704
And you offer this amazing gift to every single man, woman, and child to simply receive that gift by faith, to trust that Jesus is your son, that he died for our sin, and he rose from the dead.

29:07.744 --> 29:16.715
And Father, if there's somebody here today who has never prayed that prayer before, I pray that that would be the expression, that would be their hard cry to you right now.

29:17.657 --> 29:21.842
And perhaps they'll come to know you for the very first time as Lord and Savior.

29:22.242 --> 29:29.774
and that they can come up and rejoice with the rest of us in remembering all that Jesus has done for us by partaking of the communion elements.

29:30.455 --> 29:44.316
As a follower, we thank you again for every person who's here today, and we do thank you for communion because it is a very special time, a significant time for us to remember, reflect, and appreciate all that Jesus has done for us.

29:44.897 --> 29:47.200
As a follower, we commit this time to you now in Jesus' name.

29:47.961 --> 29:48.402
Amen.

